        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" you do? You can:"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" - splice from the (mpeg or whatever - let's just assume that the video"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"   input is either digital or does the encoding on its own - like they"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"   pretty much all do) video input into a pipe (remember: no copies - the"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"   video input will just DMA directly into memory, and splice will just"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"   set up the pages in the pipe buffer)"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" - tee that pipe to split it up"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" - splice one end to a file (ie \"save the compressed stream to disk\")"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" - splice the other end to a real-time video decoder window for your"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"   real-time viewing pleasure."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" Linus: Now, the advantage of splice()/tee() is that you can"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" do zero-copy movement of data, and unlike sendfile() you can"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" do it on _arbitrary_ data (and, as shown by \"tee()\", it's more"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" than just sending the data to somebody else: you can duplicate"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" the data and choose to forward it to two or more different"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" users - for things like logging etc.)."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
